snippet.textDisplay: 😂 nailtech here. The dust collector isn't supposed to act like a vacuum after the fact, like you used it in this video. It's more so for when you do acrylic or gel nails, and file with a nail drill. You take the hose and point it in the direction of the clients hand. It sucks it up as you file, to reduce the amount of dust in the air and lungs of the tech who files nails all day. But typically techs like to use dust collectors that are either built flat into the table, or those that instead of a hose it looks more like a vent. And the tech will file your nails over top of the dust collector and it will suck the dust right in from under the hand.
snippet.textOriginal: 😂 nailtech here. The dust collector isn't supposed to act like a vacuum after the fact, like you used it in this video. It's more so for when you do acrylic or gel nails, and file with a nail drill. You take the hose and point it in the direction of the clients hand. It sucks it up as you file, to reduce the amount of dust in the air and lungs of the tech who files nails all day. But typically techs like to use dust collectors that are either built flat into the table, or those that instead of a hose it looks more like a vent. And the tech will file your nails over top of the dust collector and it will suck the dust right in from under the hand.
